(151, 1, '2021-02-27 17:14:48', '2021-02-27 17:14:48', '<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Prerequisites</strong></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>By entering as a team into the tournament, all players acknowledge that they fully agree to the rules and terms of the tournament.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>All players also acknowledge they are 16 years old and above inorder to legally participate in the tournament.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>By failing to comply with prerequisites users will get eliminated from the tournament as well as banned</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Organizers Events take the right to validate and confirm the details for each user before, during, and after the tournament takes place. If any irregularities are found at a player or at one or more members of the team, respective tournament organizers (“TO”) take the right to disqualify any player or the whole team from the tournament even after the tournament is finished.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>When in doubt about anything regarding rules or if you have any questions related to the following tournament, please contact the official discord channel which has been given to you.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Quick Rules</strong></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>The tournament format depends on the event and it is specified within the event rules seen under the Tournament Overview Format section.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>When in a tournament, if a player or all team members don’t join the match within the 10 minutes connect game period, the match will count as an auto-loss and the opposing team will win the match or has to play with fewer players.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Stages</strong><ul><li><strong>The tournament is divided into 3 stages</strong></li><li>Open qualifications</li><li>Group stage</li><li>Play-off</li></ul></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>First stage - Open qualifications</strong><ul><li>Open qualifications are held on faceit.com</li><li>Players and teams should be from the SEA region.</li></ul></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Second stage</strong> <strong>-</strong> <strong>Group stage</strong><ul><li>8 teams will be playing in the group stage(8 direct invited teams and 2 from open qualifiers)</li><li>Round robin format will be followed for the Group stage where in all the games will be Bo3</li></ul></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>&nbsp;Third stage - Play-off</strong><ul><li>Based on the scores earned by the teams during the group stage, they will be placed in the play-off brackets accordingly.</li><li>Teams having higher points will be placed in the upper brackets of the play-offs followed by the teams in the lower bracket.</li><li>Bottom two teams will be eliminated.</li></ul></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Game Format</strong><ul><li>Dates: March 1st - March 22nd</li><li>The tournament is divided into 2 stages:</li></ul></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Group Stage</strong><ul><li>Dates: March 1st – March 14th</li><li>Round Robin format with 10 Teams (8 Direct Invited teams and 2 teams from faceit.com open qualifiers)</li><li>Top four teams will advance to the Upper bracket of the playoffs</li><li>Teams 5-8 will be placed in the lower bracket of the playoffs</li><li>Bottom 2 teams will be eliminated from the tournament.</li></ul></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Play-offs Stage</strong><ul><li>Dates: March 16th - March 24th</li><li>Double elimination format for 8 teams</li><li>All matches are Bo3</li><li>Grand Finals is Bo5</li></ul></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Teams &amp; Players</strong><ul><li>A team must consist of a minimum of 5 players.</li><li>Real nicks must be used.</li><li>Tags must be used.</li><li>Standins can be used online, max 3 in tournament</li><li>Standins must not be a member of another team in the tournament.</li><li>Standins must use a Standin tag before their nicknames.</li><li>If standins are to be used, Admins must be notified at least 12 hours prior to the game.</li></ul></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Players Information</strong><ul><li>Players must send to the tournament organizer all the necessary information about the team and players at the official request of the organizer.</li></ul></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Selection order</strong><ul><li>Automatic coin toss is used on the first map, on the second map&nbsp; the&nbsp; opposite command has the right of first choice.</li><li>On odd maps, a rule similar to the first map applies, on even - the &nbsp; &nbsp; second</li></ul></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Game Servers</strong><ul><li>Default server is Singapore but any other server can be selected if both the teams and admin agree.</li><li>The game can be postponed for a maximum of 1 hour from the time of&nbsp; its official start because of the delay of the previous game.</li><li>In case of the delay of a match for more than 1 hour - the teams have the right to ask to postpone the match for another day at time convenient for them.</li><li>The game will be hosted by the admin at least 15 minutes before the first game is to start.</li><li>&nbsp;A representative from each team must be in contact with an admin 15 mins before the game is supposed to start (Team Captain or Manager).</li><li>&nbsp;All the players should be in the game 5 minutes before the game will start.</li></ul></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Game Penalty</strong><ul><li>5 mins:take 30 penalty points</li><li>10 mins:take 70 penalty points</li><li>15mins:take 110 penalty points</li><li>20 mins:take Def Lose map 1</li></ul></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Map-Setting</strong>&nbsp;<ul><li><strong>The following settings are to be used every game:</strong><ul><li>Lobby password: Will be shared on discord server after lobby creation.&nbsp;</li><li>Cheats: Off</li><li>Bots: Off</li><li>All Chat: Off</li><li>Version: Tournament</li><li>Series: BO3</li><li>Finals: BO5</li><li>Gamemode: Captains Mode</li><li>Starting Team: Decided before the game</li><li>Punishments: None</li><li>Default Server: Singapore</li><li>Spectators: Tour Ticket</li><li>Dota TV Delay: 5 mins</li><li>The version to play is the current Tournament Version.</li><li>The mode to be played is CM.</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Team/Player Behavior</strong><ul><li>Flaming and bad-mouthing are not allowed.</li><li>The usage of all-chat should be used to a minimum.</li><li>No offensive nicknames are allowed.</li><li>Players should, while in game, use their official nicks</li><li>Teams should, while in game, use their official tag</li></ul></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Streaming and spectating</strong><ul><li>No streaming allowed except for streamers chosen by administrators</li><li>Only chosen streamers, producers and admins will be allowed in the spectator-spots.</li><li><strong>Game streaming languages:</strong><ul><li><strong>English</strong></li><li><strong>Russian</strong></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Disconnects, pauses and crashes</strong><ul><li>Pausing is not allowed during picks unless the captain disconnects.</li><li>If the game crashes during the picks, the game will be remade and the same picks will be picked.</li><li>Players have rights to pause the game if needed. Be sure to announce the pause in all-chat a few seconds before if not an emergency.</li><li>The reason for the pause must be reasonable. Both teams must agree on resuming before resuming the game.</li><li>If a player disconnects, the player’s team should pause the game right away.</li><li>A team has the right to 10 minutes worth of pause per map. (per team and per map) After that, the opponent team can resume unless the admin stated otherwise.</li><li>If teams disconnect from the game completely and do not have any chance connect to the game again:</li><li>If the advantage of one of the teams is less than 15 000 - This map should be restart</li><li>&nbsp;If&nbsp; the advantage of one of the teams is more than 15 000 - This team is winning on this map</li></ul></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Game end</strong><ul><li>The game is over when either team’s Ancient is destroyed or one of the team types “GG” in all chat.</li></ul></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Rules about awards for matches</strong><ul><li>Winning team gets 3 points</li><li>Losing team gets no points</li></ul></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Betting</strong><ul><li>No players, team managers, staff or management of attending organizations may be involved in betting or gambling, associate with betters or gamblers, or provide anyone any information that may assist betting or gambling, either directly or indirectly, for any of the tournament matches or the tournament in general.</li></ul></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>&nbsp;Additional rule</strong><ul><li>Any rules can be changed or added during the event by the admins.</li></ul></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->', 'Competition details', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '107-revision-v1', '', '', '2021-02-27 17:14:48', '2021-02-27 17:14:48', '', 107, 'http://onestopdota2.com/107-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
